The South African Weather Service (SAWS) has forecast a slight drop in temperature accompanied by isolated showers in the eastern parts of KwaZulu-Natal on Sunday evening. Forecaster Stacey Colborne says the cold and cloudy weather conditions will persist into Monday. “We are only expecting some cloud cover to come through from later this [Sunday] afternoon into the evening. We are expecting some isolated showers and rain mostly towards the eastern parts of KwaZulu-Natal for this evening.” “Looking ahead into Monday, you can expect some cloudy to cool and cold conditions over the province, with a 30% chance of showers and rain expected over eastern KwaZulu-Natal,” explains Colborne. Below is the full weather report: 